content":"REPLYING TO Fighterpilotmafia WHO SAID: <u>\" You know what I&apos;d really like to see?  At the very least, a form that the patient has to sign with the statement:    \"I hereby acknowledge that in proceeding with said abortion, I am putting to death a human child.\"    Just to admit it.  Just to throw the outrageous claim of &apos;choice&apos; out the window.  Sure, it&apos;s a choice.  But it is a choice to kill a baby.\"</u>  Since you have avoided answering this before, please explain why the government should be able to FORCE a woman to put up with the pain and risk of carrying and delivering a baby but YOU can not be FORCE to take less risky and painful actions to save a life? For example   Donate blood    Donate bone marrow   Donate skin Or even actions such as donate a kidney or a part of the liver. ","user_id":"rayld2","fromReply":[33,41,57,61],"toReply":[1,4,7,21,25]},{"topic":"abortion_as_rights_or_choices","thread_id":"5531905206_6420099791001","post_id":33,"time":"Sat 06 September 2008 04:34 PM","content":"REPLYING TO rayld2 WHO SAID: <u>\"  Since you have avoided answering this before, please explain why the government should be able to FORCE a woman to put up with the pain and risk of carrying and delivering a baby but YOU can not be FORCE to take less risky and painful actions to save a life? For example   Donate blood    Donate bone marrow   Donate skin Or even actions such as donate a kidney or a part of the liver.\"</u>  The woman put herself in the position to be pregnant in the first place.  Does she have any responsibility to avoid getting pregnant (the only sure way is abstinence) until she is ready to have kids or is it everyone else&apos;s responsibility to pick up her slack so she won&apos;t murder her child because she just had to have sex? ","user_id":"Silverbusa","fromReply":[36,50,52,55],"toReply":[32]},{"topic":"abortion_as_rights_or_choices","thread_id":"5531905206_6420099791001","post_id":34,"time":"Sat 06 September 2008 0